Repositories in Spring Data JPA

In Spring Data JPA, a repository is a special interface that abstracts data access logic.

Instead of writing boilerplate DAO code (EntityManager, Session, CRUD queries), you just define a repository interface, and Spring generates the implementation at runtime.

Repositories allow you to interact with the database using simple Java methods.

Example:

@Repository
public interface StudentRepository extends JpaRepository<Student, Long> {
    List<Student> findByName(String name);
}